# Ruigang Jiang

### MPH Biostatistics Student | Data Analysis | AI for Public Health

I am a Master of Public Health student in Biostatistics at Emory University, Rollins School of Public Health. My work focuses on using statistical methods, data analysis, and artificial intelligence to address real-world public health challenges.

I am especially interested in building practical, data-driven tools that support healthcare decision-making, public health communication, and risk assessment. My recent projects include LLM-powered public health tools, retrieval-augmented generation systems, dietary assessment using AI models, and interactive data visualization.

